# 2p_ctf_score_limit — verifies the host-configured score_limit gates
# CTF round-end. Pre-fix the M5-era "+5 team_score per capture"
# against a clamped CTF default of 5 made the round end on the first
# capture; post-fix capture adds +1 to team_score so score_limit
# directly = captures-to-win, matching FFA / TDM (which use
# kills-to-win).
#
# Setup: score_limit=3 (per the runner's cfg). Host stands on the
# RED home flag. arm_carry forces flag 1 (BLUE) into a CARRIED state
# with the host as carrier; the next ctf_step tick sees the
# "carrying enemy flag + own flag home + touching own home flag"
# precondition and fires ctf_capture (team_score++).
#
# Score progression:
#   tick 200 — capture 1 → team_score=1, round must stay ACTIVE
#   tick 240 — capture 2 → team_score=2, round must stay ACTIVE
#   tick 280 — capture 3 → team_score=3 = score_limit → round ENDS
#              (SUMMARY phase + map-vote follow-up)

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/host_ctf_score_limit
network host 24037
name HostRed

# Park on the RED home flag (Crossfire RED flag is at x=480, y=1520,
# platform top at y=1536). Pelvis at y=1496 puts chest within 36 px
# of the staff segment (the new touch-box rule from
# tests/shots/net/run_ctf_pickup.sh).
spawn_at 480 1496

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

at 140 shot t140_round_start

# Capture 1. arm_carry puts BLUE in our hands; ctf_step on the
# next tick sees us touching the RED home flag with the BLUE flag
# and fires ctf_capture.
at 180 arm_carry 1 0
at 220 shot t220_after_capture1

# Capture 2. The captured flag was sent home on capture 1, so we
# can immediately re-arm it.
at 240 arm_carry 1 0
at 270 shot t270_after_capture2

# Capture 3 — this should hit score_limit=3 and end the round.
at 290 arm_carry 1 0
at 320 shot t320_after_capture3_round_end

at 600 end
